{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781151878871,"sessionID":"ses_14b140814ffe4N8PH7Vn6Su76Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_TXWQI47d5jSrkGaGXcVZX1Ia","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"packed|BM25|field weights|weights|fts|search","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 73 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Shipped packed-inmemory BM25 engine with typed-array postings, BM25F field weighting, explicit engine selection, budget tests, and fixture-backed baseline eval evidence.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"014-packed-bm25-field-weights summary\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 13:     recent_action: \"Shipped packed-inmemory BM25 fallback with typed postings and BM25F weighting\"\n\n  Line 17:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/bm25-index.ts\"\n\n  Line 19:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/fixtures/bm25-packed-fixture.ts\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/bm25-packed-inmemory.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       session_id: \"scaffold-014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 42: | **Spec Folder** | 014-packed-bm25-field-weights |\n\n  Line 52: Status: SHIPPED. The reserved `packed-inmemory` BM25 engine now has a real packed postings implementation, BM25F field weighting, explicit selection logging, fixture budget gates, and a baseline comparison against legacy and FTS5 scoring.\n\n  Line 56: The packed engine stores per-document length and term keys only. Term frequencies live in a term dictionary that builds append-only numeric postings during warmup, then compacts them into typed arrays for search. After finalization, mutable construction arrays are cleared; later incremental updates hydrate only the touched term back into mutable form.\n\n  Line 58: Search reads postings for query terms instead of scanning every document. Each posting carries total, title, trigger phrase, path, and body frequencies. BM25F scoring multiplies those field frequencies by the shared field weights at query time, so callers can override weights without rebuilding the index.\n\n  Line 64: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/bm25-index.ts` | Modified | Added packed storage, typed-array postings, BM25F scoring, selection logging, and packed warmup finalization |\n\n  Line 65: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/bm25-baseline.ts` | Modified | Added a fixture-backed engine comparison helper for legacy, packed, and FTS5 metrics |\n\n  Line 66: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/fixtures/bm25-packed-fixture.ts` | Created | Added current-corpus and relevance fixtures for budget and baseline evaluation |\n\n  Line 67: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/bm25-packed-inmemory.vitest.ts` | Created | Added budget, BM25F, engine-toggle, and baseline parity tests |\n\n  Line 76: Delivered as an additive in-memory engine path. `legacy-inmemory` remains selectable, `packed-inmemory` now uses the packed implementation, and `auto` chooses the packed in-memory fallback when an in-memory fallback instance is needed. Selection is logged once per routing reason.\n\n  Line 78: The FTS5 channel is unchanged. The packed fallback mirrors the FTS5 field-priority intent with title > trigger phrases > path > body weights from `BM25_FIELD_WEIGHTS`.\n\n  Line 89: | Use typed arrays after warmup | Query-time search only needs compact numeric postings; mutable warmup arrays are discarded after finalization |\n\n  Line 90: | Keep weights query-time tunable | Title weighting can be restored without rebuilding the index or changing the FTS5 channel |\n\n  Line 102: | `npx vitest run tests/bm25-packed-inmemory.vitest.ts` | PASS, 1 test file, 4 tests |\n\n  Line 105: | BM25 baseline comparison | PASS: packed MRR@5 1.0000, NDCG@10 1.0000, Recall@20 1.0000, HitRate@1 1.0000; legacy MRR@5 0.9000; FTS5 MRR@5 1.0000 |\n\n  Line 108: | Strict spec validation | PASS: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights --strict`, exit 0 |\n\n  Line 116: 1. **3x projection exceeds 150 MB RSS.** The current corpus gate passed, so the minisearch contingency is not triggered for this phase. If 3x scale becomes a hard requirement, open a separate scale packet.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights/spec.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Feature Specification: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights [template:level_1/spec.md]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Implement the reserved packed-inmemory BM25 engine (typed-array postings) and BM25F per-field weighting so the fallback lexical channel is memory-safe and relevance-equivalent to FTS5.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"packed bm25\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"bm25f field weights\"\n\n  Line 13:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 16:     recent_action: \"Packed in-memory BM25 engine shipped with BM25F weighting and measured budget evidence\"\n\n  Line 17:     next_safe_action: \"Monitor packed fallback warmups\"\n\n  Line 22:       session_id: \"scaffold-014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 29: # Feature Specification: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights\n\n  Line 53: | **Parent Packet** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement |\n\n  Line 62: The in-memory BM25 fallback channel has two latent defects at the measured corpus (10,245 docs, 69.2 MB indexed text). First, the legacy engine stores full token arrays per document (bm25-index.ts:197-207), an estimated 300-600 MB of heap if it ever warms the full corpus - a standing RAM hazard for the daemon whenever memory_fts is absent. Second, it flattens title/content/triggers/path into one field (bm25-index.ts:151-172), silently losing the title-x10 weighting that the FTS5 channel applies via bm25(memory_fts,10,5,2,1) - the engine slot packed-inmemory is reserved but unimplemented (bm25-index.ts:53,487-493) and BM25_FIELD_WEIGHTS is exported but unused there (:73-78). Source evidence: z_future/sqlite-to-turso 004 - gap-alternatives.md section 3.\n\n  Line 65: The fallback lexical channel becomes memory-bounded and relevance-equivalent to the FTS5 primary, with weights staying query-time tunable - strengthening today's resilience story and removing the hard FTS5 dependency for any future backend.\n\n  Line 75: - BM25F per-field weighting consuming the exported BM25_FIELD_WEIGHTS\n\n  Line 81: - Third-party search libraries (minisearch contingency stays a documented trigger, not scope)\n\n  Line 88: | `mcp_server/lib/search/bm25-index.ts` | Modify | Packed engine in the reserved slot + BM25F scoring |\n\n  Line 89: | `mcp_server/lib/eval/bm25-baseline.ts` (+fixtures) | Modify | Eval comparison legacy vs packed vs FTS5 |\n\n  Line 102: | REQ-001 | Packed engine warms the full current corpus within 150 MB RSS and 10 s, with relevance >= the legacy engine on the bm25-baseline eval | Measured spike recorded; budget breach fails the phase and fires the minisearch contingency decision |\n\n  Line 108: | REQ-002 | BM25F field weighting applied with query-time-tunable weights matching the FTS5 channel's intent (title > triggers > path > content) | Eval shows the title-weighting signal restored vs the flattened legacy engine |\n\n  Line 109: | REQ-003 | Engine selection (legacy/packed/auto) is explicit, logged, and the legacy engine remains available behind the existing engine flag | Toggle test; no silent engine switch |\n\n  Line 117: - **SC-001**: Fallback channel relevance parity: packed+BM25F within agreed eval delta of the FTS5 channel on the golden set.\n\n  Line 137: - Is the minisearch contingency acceptable as a dependency if the packed spike breaches budget, or is buy-not-build excluded?\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights/plan.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights [template:level_1/plan.md]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Implement the reserved packed-inmemory engine (term dictionary + typed-array postings), add BM25F per-field weighting from the exported weights, and gate on measured RAM/warmup budgets plus the bm25-baseline eval.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"014-packed-bm25-field-weights plan\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 14:     next_safe_action: \"Use packed-inmemory for fallback validation\"\n\n  Line 19:       session_id: \"scaffold-014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 26: # Implementation Plan: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights\n\n  Line 52: Implement the reserved packed-inmemory engine (term dictionary + typed-array postings), add BM25F per-field weighting from the exported weights, and gate on measured RAM/warmup budgets plus the bm25-baseline eval.\n\n  Line 67: - [x] Tests passing: `npm run build` and `npx vitest run tests/bm25-packed-inmemory.vitest.ts`\n\n  Line 81: - **BM25F scoring**: Per-field weights, query-time tunable\n\n  Line 85: warmup batches -> packed postings build -> search() inverted-index lookups -> BM25F scores -> existing fusion channel unchanged.\n\n  Line 106: - [x] RAM/warmup spike on packed layout at 1x and 3x corpus\n\n  Line 111: - [x] BM25F field weighting\n\n  Line 149: - **Procedure**: Engine flag keeps legacy as default until parity + budgets pass; packed engine is additive.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights/tasks.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Tasks: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights [template:level_1/tasks.md]\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"014-packed-bm25-field-weights tasks\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 13:     recent_action: \"All implementation and verification tasks completed with measured packed BM25 evidence\"\n\n  Line 14:     next_safe_action: \"Monitor packed fallback telemetry\"\n\n  Line 19:       session_id: \"scaffold-014-packed-bm25-field-weights\"\n\n  Line 26: # Tasks: Packed In-Memory BM25 Engine with Field Weights\n\n  Line 50: - [x] T001 Spike: packed postings layout, RSS measured at 1x/3x corpus. Evidence: current corpus fixture 10,245 docs, 69.2 MB indexed text, RSS spike 111,017,984 bytes, warmup 809.17 ms; 3x projection 30,735 docs, RSS spike 247,676,928 bytes, warmup 2,689 ms.\n\n  Line 51: - [x] T002 Eval baseline: legacy engine + FTS5 channel on bm25-baseline harness. Evidence: packed MRR@5 1.0000, legacy MRR@5 0.9000, FTS5 MRR@5 1.0000 on the fixture-backed comparison.\n\n  Line 59: - [x] T003 Packed engine implementation in the reserved packed-inmemory slot. Evidence: `BM25Index` supports `packed-inmemory`, stores per-document lengths and term keys, and materializes typed-array postings via `finalizePackedPostings()`.\n\n  Line 60: - [x] T004 BM25F per-field weighting from BM25_FIELD_WEIGHTS. Evidence: packed scoring consumes title, trigger phrase, path, and body weights with query-time overrides.\n\n  Line 61: - [x] T005 Engine selection (legacy/packed/auto) explicit + logged. Evidence: toggle test asserts legacy, packed, and auto selection plus console selection logs.\n\n  Line 69: - [x] T006 Scoring parity suite packed-vs-legacy on fixtures. Evidence: `npx vitest run tests/bm25-packed-inmemory.vitest.ts` passed 1 file, 4 tests.\n\n  Line 71: - [x] T008 Eval comparison recorded; minisearch contingency decision row if budgets breached. Evidence: current corpus passed, so contingency is not triggered; 3x projection exceeds 150 MB and is recorded as a scale risk outside the current P0 gate.\n","metadata":{"matches":73,"truncated":false},"title":"packed|BM25|field weights|weights|fts|search","time":{"start":1781151878856,"end":1781151878870}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c385f40c41ef242016a2a3886c04c81918c55edae8c31e716"}},"id":"prt_eb4ecceb8001xBdCfDg7sxVR63","sessionID":"ses_14b140814ffe4N8PH7Vn6Su76Z","messageID":"msg_eb4ecba80001GGs167C92VSd3o"}}
